Explanation:
- The controller method is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/consumer/notifications", method = RequestMethod.GET)
  in NotificationsController#getConsumerNotifications. That defines the endpoint path as "/consumer/notifications" and explicitly restricts the mapping to the GET method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping in this controller file to add a prefix, and no other provided files indicate a servlet or controller prefix; therefore the full path is exactly "/consumer/notifications".
- Per the instructions, I did not assume framework behaviors (such as automatic handling of HEAD or OPTIONS). Based strictly on the source code annotation, only GET is declared acceptable; all other methods are not declared and thus marked not acceptable.
